data.enText: the main or general meaning of a piece of writing, a speech or a conversation
to get (= understand) the gist of an argument

data.chText: 我未听到讲座的开头——给我讲讲他说话的要点好吗？
data.enText: I missed the beginning of the lecture─can you give me the gist of what he said?

data.chText: 对不起，我还不太明白你的意思。
data.enText: I'm afraid I don't quite follow your gist (= what you really mean) .

tr: the choicest or most essential or most vital part of some idea or experience
example: the gist of the prosecutor's argument
the heart and soul of the Republican Party

tr: the central meaning or theme of a speech or literary work

value.def: The gist of a speech, conversation, or piece of writing is its general meaning.

example.ex: He related the gist of his conversation to Naseby.
example.tran: 他将他谈话的要点告诉了纳斯比。

value.tran: （发言、谈话或文章的）主旨，要点
